# Sealed Secrets — Trusted GPG Public Keys
#
# This file is a placeholder. To populate it:
#
#   1. Each team member generates a key:
#        ./scripts/generate-gpg-key.sh "Your Name" your@email.com
#
#   2. Each member exports their public key:
#        gpg --armor --export your@email.com > your@email.com.pub.asc
#
#   3. The admin concatenates all public keys into this file:
#        cat alice@corp.com.pub.asc bob@corp.com.pub.asc > sealed-secrets-trusted-keys.asc
#
#   4. Create the Kubernetes Secret:
#        kubectl create secret generic sealed-secrets-gpg-keys \
#          -n kube-system \
#          --from-file=secrets.io=sealed-secrets-trusted-keys.asc
#
# The file format is one or more ASCII-armored GPG public key blocks.
# Do NOT put plaintext instructions between the PGP markers.
# BEGIN_PGP_MARKER
# Replace this file with actual exported public keys before use.
# END_PGP_MARKER
